# SkillForge20 Changelog

---

## 2026-05-28 — Session: Phase 1-5 initial build

Problem: Project did not exist.
Fix: Built Phase 1 through Phase 5 per CLAUDE.md build order.
Reason: New project bootstrap.
Result: DB schema, server, intake wizard, Today tab with 4-card layout, practice generation, self-correct generation, audio (TTS + speech recognition) all passing acceptance criteria.

---

## 2026-05-28 — Session: Phase 6 — Plan and Log Tabs

Problem: Plan and Log tabs showed placeholders; no export/import capability.
Fix:
  - Added GET /api/skills/:id/plan endpoint returning PlanSessionDetail[] (sessions joined with subskill names)
  - Added POST /api/sessions/skill/:skillId/advance for plan advancement check and execution
  - Created server/routes/export.ts with GET /:skillId (JSON download) and POST /import
  - Created PlanTab.tsx, WeekGrid.tsx, SessionSlot.tsx for 7-week grid with advancement panel
  - Created LogTab.tsx, SessionHistory.tsx, HoursProgress.tsx for full session history and export
  - Updated App.tsx to wire Plan and Log tabs, added Import Skill button to left rail
  - Added PlanSessionDetail type to src/types/index.ts
  - Added plan, export API methods to src/lib/api.ts
Reason: Phase 6 acceptance criteria require functional plan grid, advancement logic, log history, and export/import.
Result: Plan tab shows 7-week grid with current week highlighted, session status (complete/active/planned/skipped), Check Advance button with backend recommendation. Log tab shows hours progress bar, session history with whatDidntWork and self-correct excerpts, Export JSON download, Import JSON upload. TypeScript clean. All endpoints verified.

---

## 2026-05-28 — Session: Phase 7 — Assessment

Problem: Assess tab showed a placeholder; no assessment capability existed.
Fix:
  - Added runAssessmentGeneration() to server/lib/prompts.ts; ASSESSMENT_SYSTEM prompt derives threshold from done criteria text
  - Created server/routes/assessments.ts: POST /generate (AI call), POST /:skillId (save result + update floor/ceiling), GET /:skillId (list history)
  - Mounted /api/assessments in server/index.ts
  - Added AssessmentContent, AssessmentItem, AssessmentRow types to src/types/index.ts
  - Built AssessTab.tsx (intro/generating/running/saving/done phases), AssessmentRunner.tsx (item-by-item reveal+score flow), ResultCard.tsx (score breakdown)
  - Wired AssessTab into App.tsx with onAssessmentSaved calling refreshToken() to update TopBar immediately
Reason: Phase 7 acceptance criteria require assessment derived from done criteria, floor/ceiling cleared states persisted and reflected in TopBar.
Result: AI extracts threshold from floor/ceiling text (e.g. "70%" → floorThreshold:70), generates 4-12 items testing only practiced subskills, tooEarlyWarning when < 10h logged. Submission updates floor_cleared/ceiling_cleared in DB. TopBar shows ✓ Floor / ✓ Ceiling immediately. TypeScript clean.

