## 2026-05-28 — Session: Phase 8 — Polish

Problem: App had rough edges: no settings, no skill-type color differentiation in left rail, layout could shift on token load, no retry on TodayTab error, wizard deconstruction showed only a blank spinner.
Fix:
  - Added GET /api/settings endpoint returning apiKeyConfigured boolean
  - Added Settings toggle in left rail with inline panel (API key status, version, DB type)
  - Added skill-type colored dot to each skill button in left rail (language=blue, instrument=amber, concept=violet, create=green, fix=orange, do=red)
  - TopBar skeleton renders immediately while token loads (prevents layout shift)
  - TodayTab error state now has Retry button
  - Wizard deconstructing step shows animated 6-step progress bar cycling through "Analyzing skill type..." → "Finalizing sessions..."
  - TodayTab grid changed to grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 for responsive stacking
Reason: Phase 8 acceptance criteria — loading context, error recovery, always-visible top bar, settings, skill type colors, responsive layout.
Result: All 8 phases complete. TypeScript clean. Full end-to-end flow working: intake → deconstruction → practice → self-correct → plan → log → export/import → assessment → cleared states.

