## 2026-05-28 — Session: v2.0 — FIX 1-8

Problem: Six confirmed bugs from v1.0 usage: practice content regenerated on tab switch, weekly plan had duplicate subskills across week pairs, session state lived only in React local state (reset on tab switch), session log entries were not expandable/editable/deletable, hours_logged never updated, and practice card had an internal scrollbar.
Fix:
  FIX 1 — Schema migration: ALTER TABLE session_logs added practice_content TEXT and session_state TEXT DEFAULT 'idle'.
  FIX 2 (BUG-01) — Moved practice AI generation from useEffect into startSession() handler. On mount, PracticeCard checks DB for existing practice_content via GET /api/sessions/active; if present, renders from DB with no AI call. POST /sessions/start now accepts and stores practiceContent JSON.
  FIX 3 (BUG-03) — Added session_state column with explicit state machine (idle/active/logging/self_correct/complete). TodayTab fetches sessionLogId, sessionState, practiceContent, startedAt from DB on every render and passes as props; children call onStateChange() to trigger reload. SelfCorrectCard unlocks on sessionState === "self_correct" instead of local flag.
  FIX 4 (BUG-05) — Replaced all hours_logged increments with idempotent SUM subquery: UPDATE skills SET hours_logged = (SELECT COALESCE(SUM(minutes_logged),0)/60.0 FROM session_logs WHERE skill_id=?) at PATCH /:id/practice, PATCH /:id/self-correct, PATCH /:id/edit, and DELETE /:id.
  FIX 5 — New PracticeOutputForm with per-task rows (PracticeTaskRow), extra step rows (ExtraStepRow), and auto-calculated time summary (TimeSummaryTable). Task list pre-populated from frozen practice_content.tasks. Save blocked if whatDidntWork is empty.
  FIX 6 (BUG-04) — SessionLogEntry rewrote as expandable card: collapsed shows S[N]/subskill/rating/date/time; expanded shows practice content, v2.0 task table (with fallback to v1.0 flat text), self-correct output, Edit/Delete buttons. Edit pre-fills PracticeOutputForm. Delete has confirm dialog and calls DELETE /:id.
  FIX 7 (BUG-06) — PracticeCard now has two views toggled by showFull state: summary (task chips only, no scroll) and full (fullInstructions in overflow-y-auto max-h-56 block). CardBody has no max-h constraint.
  FIX 8 (BUG-02) — Updated DECONSTRUCT_SYSTEM and deconstructTool schema to output phase-bucketed arrays (foundation/depth/stress), each 4-8 distinct subskills. runDeconstruction() flattens buckets back to SubskillDraft[] for confirm-plan. Fixed distributeSessions() to assign each subskill once before overflow; overflow uses priority-1 pool only instead of cycling entire pool. Added POST /api/skills/:id/regenerate-plan endpoint. Added Regenerate Plan button with confirmation dialog to PlanTab.
Reason: All 6 bugs confirmed in v1.0 real usage per CLAUDE.md bug registry. v2.0 build contract specified exact fix approach for each.
Result: Full session flow works from Start Session through self-correct and hours update without any AI call on tab return. Log entries expandable, editable, deletable with hours recalculation. Practice card fits in 2x2 grid without scrollbar. New skills get distinct phase subskills; existing skill can regenerate plan via UI button. TypeScript clean. Server healthy.

