## 2026-05-30 — Session: v2.2 — BUG-11, BUG-12, BUG-13, Features, /start fix

Problem: Week 7 showed foundation subskills instead of assessment sessions (BUG-11). Left rail skill name truncated and Definition of Done was not visible (BUG-12). Session logs written with week_number = 0 (BUG-13). No initial report prompt after plan generation. No barrier management during active skill. POST /start returned HTML 500 on any SQLite error.
Fix:
  BUG-11 — Added insertAssessSubskills() helper in skills.ts. Creates 4 DB-backed subskill rows (week_phase=assess) inside the plan generation transaction. Both confirm-plan and regenerate-plan call it and pass assess refs to distributeSessions(). Removed the broken if(phase==="assess") override that fell back to priority-1 foundation subskills.
  BUG-12 — App.tsx: skill name button changed to items-start, span changed from truncate to break-words. Left rail aside width converted from w-52 to dynamic state with drag handle (position:absolute, right edge, cursor-col-resize), clamped 200-400px, persisted in localStorage key sf20-rail-width. SessionMetaPanel.tsx: Definition of Done section added below last-session line, reads skill.done_floor and skill.done_ceiling from SkillContext, text-xs, break-words, no truncation.
  BUG-13 — sessions.ts /start route: added week_number to session_logs INSERT, reads plan.week_number ?? 1 from already-fetched PlanSessionRow. DB migration: ALTER TABLE session_logs ADD COLUMN week_number INTEGER DEFAULT 1 run directly against skillforge.db via bun:sqlite.
  FEATURE InitialReportModal — New src/components/shared/InitialReportModal.tsx. TodayTab checks localStorage flag sf20-initial-saved-[skillId] and token.hoursLogged===0 after data loads; shows modal if not flagged. Save button fetches /api/export/[skillId] as blob, downloads as SF20-initial.json. Skip or Save both set the localStorage flag. Shows once per skill ID.
  FEATURE BarriersPanel — New server/routes/barriers.ts (GET/PATCH/POST). Registered in server/index.ts at /api/barriers. New src/components/log/BarriersPanel.tsx: resolved checkbox (optimistic update with rollback), inline mitigation text input (saves on blur or Enter), + Add Barrier inline form (type select + text). LogTab.tsx imports and renders BarriersPanel below session history.
  /start fix — Entire /start handler wrapped in try/catch returning res.status(500).json({error:message}). plan_sessions SELECT changed from SELECT * to explicit column list. weekNumber extracted to const before transaction.
Reason: All items confirmed broken in v2.1 real usage. Fixes follow exact scope and approach from CLAUDE.md BUG registry and feature specs.
Result: Week 7 shows correct assessment sessions on new skill and Regenerate Plan. Left rail wraps text, shows DoD, resize persists. Start Session works, week_number writes correctly. New skill shows initial report prompt once. Log tab has full barrier CRUD. /start returns JSON errors instead of HTML. Build clean. DB migrated.

