## 2026-05-29 — Session: v2.1 — FIX 1-8

Problem: Four confirmed bugs from v2.0 usage: hours display out of sync across TopBar/LogTab/AssessTab (BUG-07), running timer stops on tab switch and seeds from zero on return (BUG-08), 2x2 grid cramps the practice area and duplicates the Log tab (BUG-09), Assess tab warning fires against stale 0.0h and hard-blocked the Generate Assessment button (BUG-10).
Fix:
  FIX 1 — SkillContext: Created src/context/SkillContext.tsx with SkillProvider, SkillContext, and useSkill() hook. GET /api/skills/:id returns {skill,...} so refreshSkill() extracts data.skill. Provider wraps all of MainApp in App.tsx. Null guard skips fetch when skillId is null. Clears stale data on skill switch.
  FIX 2 (BUG-07) — TopBar: Imports useSkill(), reads skill?.hours_logged from context. Falls back to token.hoursLogged until context resolves.
  FIX 3 (BUG-07) — LogTab: Removed independent fetch(/api/skills/:id) and local hoursLogged state. handleChanged() calls await refreshSkill() then refreshLogs() — delete and edit save now update all displays simultaneously.
  FIX 4 (BUG-07/10) — AssessTab: Reads skill from useSkill(). Single showDualWarning replaces tooEarly/softWarning. Warning text updated to dual 20h + 7-week requirement. Each condition goes green when met. Generate Assessment button never disabled. Week number derived from skill.created_at.
  FIX 5 (BUG-07) — SelfCorrectCard: Calls await refreshSkill() after PATCH succeeds and before onSelfCorrectSaved(). Completing a session updates TopBar, LogTab, and AssessTab hours simultaneously.
  FIX 6 (BUG-08) — Timer removal: Removed elapsed state, timerRef, timer useEffect, fmt() helper, clock display from PracticeCard. Removed startedAt prop thread. Removed elapsed prop from PracticeOutputForm, TimeSummaryTable, SessionLogEntry edit call. PracticeTaskRow: "Xm planned" renamed to "Goal: Xm". TimeSummaryTable: Wall clock row removed. minutesLogged = timeSummary.totalActual. No setInterval anywhere in the app.
  FIX 7 (BUG-09) — Layout restructure: TodayTab rewritten as 2-column resizable layout with useCallback drag handle (min 200px, max 45% viewport). Left: hint / SelfCorrectCard / complete summary. Right: PracticeCard full height — flex flex-col h-full, header shrink-0, body flex-1 overflow-y-auto, footer shrink-0 sticky Done button. SessionCard and SessionLogCard removed from TodayTab. SessionMetaPanel added to App.tsx aside.
  FIX 8 (BUG-09) — Pace indicator in SessionMetaPanel: weeks_elapsed = max(1, ceil), expected = weeks*(20/7), delta = hours-expected. On pace (grey ±0.5h), Ahead (amber), Behind (blue) with add Xm/session subtitle. New skill at 0h shows Behind. Display-only.
Reason: BUG-07 through BUG-10 confirmed in v2.0 real usage. Fix order followed exactly per CLAUDE.md v2.1 Section 9.
Result: Hours synchronized across TopBar/LogTab/AssessTab via SkillContext. No automatic timer. Two-column resizable Today tab with sticky Done button and no practice column scrollbar in summary view. Session meta and pace indicator in left rail. Generate Assessment always clickable. TypeScript clean. Build passes.

